I have not posted about fitness stuff in a long time, but a lot of people are worried about losing their gains. I suggest doing the "Evil Russian pushup program" (ignore the cringe name ty), which consists of you doing pushups daily every 30-60 minutes and is VERY effective

100% test means just doing 1 set of as many pushups as you can, this is your base number.

RI means a percentage of that number, if your test was 100 and it says RI 50% this means 50 pushups

SF means time between sets, like you do a set every 30 or  90 minutes

Do it, it works
